# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Aegis private translator (D-011 close — track stubs, ignore impl)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Public clones get the empty `rift-aegis` stub crate. TRACKED files:
# Cargo.toml, src/lib.rs, src/detect.rs (empty stub), src/snapshot.rs
# (empty stub). GITIGNORED files: src/*_private.rs (the real impl —
# detect_private.rs, snapshot_private.rs, etc.). lib.rs uses
# `#[cfg_attr(feature = "private_modules", path = "*_private.rs")]`
# to swap the module source to the real impl when the feature is on
# (src-tauri's `aegis` feature enables it). rustfmt walks `pub mod`
# regardless of cfg, so the public stubs MUST exist on disk — and they
# do. See DEFERRED.md C-014.
crates/rift-aegis/src/*_private.rs
crates/rift-aegis/target/
